        "LR = 2×10⁻⁵: After outputs adapt fastest in the sense that training loss falls to near zero very quickly, and several completions become shorter and punchier (e.g., one-line rally-style lines or tight calls to action). That comes with less stability: some answers drift off brief (Prompt 2 shifts toward generic “safety on the streets” instead of transit reliability), and some look truncated or overwrought (Prompt 5’s long fragment). So the model moves more aggressively but not always in a faithful or fluent way.\n",
