        "**Stability vs speed of adaptation**\n",
        "\n",
        "Lower learning rate (5×10⁻⁶) tends to give slower movement on the DPO objective (higher loss for longer) and more stable text: outputs stay closer to the reference behavior and change gently, with less risk of sudden topic or format breakdown.\n",
